# data-models

Primary Data Models:

1. Meetings Model (Importance Score: 85/100)
- Core fields:
  - title: Meeting identifier
  - date: Meeting occurrence timestamp
  - transcript: Raw meeting content from multiple sources
  - screenshots: Associated visual content
  - signals: Extracted insights and action items
  - participants: Attendee tracking
- Relationships:
  - Many-to-many with Documents
  - One-to-many with Signals
  - Many-to-many with Topics

2. Documents Model (Importance Score: 80/100)
- Core fields:
  - title: Document identifier
  - content: Main document body
  - version: Document revision tracking
  - signals: Extracted insights
  - tags: Classification metadata
- Relationships:
  - Many-to-many with Meetings
  - One-to-many with Signals
  - One-to-many with Versions

3. Shared Signal Architecture
- Signal Types:
  - Decisions
  - Action Items
  - Blockers
  - Risks
  - Ideas
- Signal States:
  - New
  - In Progress
  - Waiting
  - Done
  - Archived

4. Knowledge Graph Integration
- Entity Relationships:
  - Meeting-to-Meeting connections
  - Document-to-Meeting references
  - Signal cross-references
  - Topic clustering

5. Versioning System
- Document version control
- Meeting transcript revisions
- Signal evolution tracking
- Reference preservation

